{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":7910,"name":"","username":"conio","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/c/c2a13f/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-09-20T19:55:20.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello everyone,\u003cbr\u003e\nnice to meet you \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAt first I would like to say I got really impressed with the engine, nicely written and powerful.\u003cbr\u003e\nI started to experiment with it - I made my own terrain generator (I create heightmap data, store it to Image class and supply to Terrain to get it generated).\u003cbr\u003e\nHowever, in examples I noted that there is just one call for terrain to SetMaterial. What I would like to achieve is creating a terrain with different textures for different heights, eg. water, mountains, planes, etc.\u003cbr\u003e\nHow do I do that - is it possible to set terrain texture/material depending on it‚Äôs height parameter or I have to create few instances of Terrain, each with different material?\u003cbr\u003e\nThank you in advance,\u003cbr\u003e\nKonrad\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:19.713Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":186,"reads":23,"readers_count":22,"score":934.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":1378,"topic_slug":"heightmap-with-different-terrain-textures","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":313,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7911,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-20T20:59:14.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHey there Konrad,Welcome to forums! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can set different textures by generating Terrain Weights or Terrain Alpha Maps. Most terrain generator tools already has this feature to produce this type of map like the free L3DT Standard Edition by BundySoft (generate Alpha Layer):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003eL3DT Standard Edition\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://www.bundysoft.com/L3DT/downloads/standard.php\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ebundysoft.com/L3DT/downloads/standard.php\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/v4zmSNI.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"390\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCheck out the example water demo or you can find the example texture under /Data/Texture/TerrainWeight.dds\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:19.762Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":23,"readers_count":22,"score":19.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":1378,"topic_slug":"heightmap-with-different-terrain-textures","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://www.bundysoft.com/L3DT/downloads/standard.php","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Download L3DT Standard Edition","clicks":14}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7920,"name":"","username":"Bananaft","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/bananaft/{size}/222_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-21T11:03:43.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eStandard Urho terrain technique uses color texture to mix 4 detail textures. So you have two options:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGenerate this color texture, painting each height to it‚Äôs corresponding color, and then feeding it to standard TerrainBlend material.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCreate your own terrain shader, that will use vertex positions to mix detail textures.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:20.364Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":9.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":1378,"topic_slug":"heightmap-with-different-terrain-textures","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":165,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7929,"name":"","username":"conio","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/c/c2a13f/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-09-21T19:22:56.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThank you guys for help, I check it out \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:21.021Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":14.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":1378,"topic_slug":"heightmap-with-different-terrain-textures","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":313,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7966,"name":"","username":"conio","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/c/c2a13f/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-09-23T20:36:40.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eJust one small question - I looked at\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTerrain.xml\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTerrainBlend.xml\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTerrainBlend.glsl\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy question is -\u0026gt; how does the engine know which texture goes for which pixel value in TerrainWeights? As far as I see it‚Äôs not defined anywhere, Terrain.xml just says unit=0/1/2/3, setting textures for them, but there is no setting that if (pixelValue \u0026gt; x \u0026amp;\u0026amp; pixelValue \u0026lt; y) { useTexture1(); }\u003cbr\u003e\nIs it done in shader?\u003cbr\u003e\nAlso, about shader, I tried to find a reference to it in .xml, but there is none - is engine using by default same shader name as Technique name? There is TerrainBlend.xml and TerrainBlend.glsl, does it work that way?\u003cbr\u003e\nThank you for help!\u003cbr\u003e\nBests,\u003cbr\u003e\nKonrad\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:23.638Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":9.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":1378,"topic_slug":"heightmap-with-different-terrain-textures","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":313,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7977,"name":"","username":"conio","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/c/c2a13f/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-09-24T17:39:53.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHey,\u003cbr\u003e\nso, as far as I get it, in TerrainWeights.dds r stands for texture 1, g is 2 and b goes for 3?\u003cbr\u003e\nWhat about dynamic heightmap, can I attach this .xml to my in-code generated heightmap?\u003cbr\u003e\nAlso, regarding naming, is it like I wrote above, XYZ.xml gets XYZ.glsl?\u003cbr\u003e\nThank you for help,\u003cbr\u003e\nWith best regards,\u003cbr\u003e\nKonrad\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:24.431Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":4.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":1378,"topic_slug":"heightmap-with-different-terrain-textures","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summ